1
00:00:06,047 --> 00:00:08,216
CAGE

2
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:11,594
Thanks, everyone, for coming!

3
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:13,179
Did you all have fun?

4
00:00:13,304 --> 00:00:15,181
So what's happening?

5
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:16,933
I don't know...

6
00:00:28,028 --> 00:00:30,864
You're hilarious as always, Ume-chan!

7
00:00:33,908 --> 00:00:36,119
All right! We're done for today!

8
00:00:36,202 --> 00:00:37,912
Let's head home!

9
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:43,585
Hey, do you know any shops
around here that have takeout?

10
00:00:43,793 --> 00:00:46,254
Huh? Why do you ask?

11
00:00:46,963 --> 00:00:48,339
Why?

12
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:52,343
<i>'Cause we're having an after-party,
of course! Yay!</i>

13
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:56,890
Yay! Cheers!

14
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:58,433
Good job today, guys!

15
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:01,770
<i>What's this?</i>

16
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:03,813
Why are we doing this outside?

17
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:05,774
It's a party! We gotta have it outside!

18
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:09,319
-Sakura-san, it's wet everywhere.
<i>-What the hell is happening here?</i>

19
00:01:09,402 --> 00:01:11,696
Looks like it was raining a lot, huh?

20
00:02:45,748 --> 00:02:48,418
Oh! They all look delicious!

21
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:51,379
Exactly what you'd expect
at a bar district!

22
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:54,799
All right, let's dig in!

23
00:02:57,176 --> 00:02:58,386
It's good!

24
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:01,014
They're all so good!

25
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:03,725
Yeah, it's really good.

26
00:03:03,808 --> 00:03:06,561
Oh, they gave us a lemon!

27
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:08,730
You idiot! Don't squirt it on everything!

28
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:12,650
I'm surprised they can still
eat in a situation like this.

29
00:03:12,734 --> 00:03:14,027
Yeah.

30
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:17,030
Oh, you think so too, Suo-san?

31
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:18,031
Thank goodness.

32
00:03:18,114 --> 00:03:20,617
Oh, I'm on a diet. That's all.

33
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:21,618
A diet?

34
00:03:23,786 --> 00:03:25,121
<i>What's wrong with him?</i>

35
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:29,584
<i>How can he share a meal with a guy
he was fighting just a moment ago?</i>

36
00:03:30,835 --> 00:03:31,753
<i>Also...</i>

37
00:03:32,837 --> 00:03:34,964
<i>can that even be considered a fight?</i>

38
00:03:35,089 --> 00:03:37,300
<i>How is he capable of something like that?</i>

39
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:39,844
<i>I would never...</i>

40
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:42,513
Hm? What's wrong, Togame?

41
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:44,849
You're not eating at all!

42
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:53,900
I'm sorry.

43
00:03:57,528 --> 00:04:02,951
Looking back, this whole incident
started because of me.

44
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:06,663
The reason why Shishitoren
began to rot from the inside...

45
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:09,123
From yesterday's raid to today's fight...

46
00:04:09,207 --> 00:04:10,208
All of that...

47
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:13,419
I'm truly sorry for
the trouble I've caused.

48
00:04:13,503 --> 00:04:15,338
Kame-chan, but that's my...

49
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:28,726
You heard them.

50
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:30,395
What do you say, Sakura?

51
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:31,688
Huh?

52
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:34,148
You decide.

53
00:04:35,149 --> 00:04:36,025
What?

54
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:39,570
I'll accept any punishment.

55
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:43,157
That's just the right thing to do.

56
00:04:56,212 --> 00:04:59,007
You better change and become a cool guy!

57
00:04:59,757 --> 00:05:01,884
Don't you ever do lame things again!

58
00:05:03,886 --> 00:05:05,054
Got it?

59
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,313
I promise.

60
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:21,612
All right!
That settles this matter for good!

61
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:24,032
Oh, what's this?

62
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:29,370
It's fried burdock roots!

63
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:35,918
Ume-chan, you're the top, so why do
you look like you're having so much fun?

64
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:41,966
I simply like eating.

65
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:49,640
I like eating, too!

66
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:51,142
Curry is my favorite!

67
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:52,185
How about you?

68
00:05:52,351 --> 00:05:54,395
I like omelet rice.

69
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:57,273
But rather than the food...

70
00:05:57,356 --> 00:06:01,027
I like being with everyone
and having fun together while eating.

71
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:04,947
We talk about stuff, laugh like idiots,

72
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:08,409
and feel like all the bad things
don't matter anymore.

73
00:06:08,534 --> 00:06:12,038
Spending time like that
is what makes me happy the most.

74
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:15,541
That's why I'm having
so much fun right now.

75
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,418
And, well...

76
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:21,714
that has nothing to do
with me being at the top.

77
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:26,135
I knew it. That's right.

78
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:28,721
<i>I remember.</i>

79
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:31,724
<i>I was already having fun
before I became the top.</i>

80
00:06:31,808 --> 00:06:34,936
<i>I was having fun, too,
when everyone was smiling.</i>

81
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:37,855
<i>But I didn't realize that back then...</i>

82
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:42,193
<i>so I thought I would have
even more fun being the top.</i>

83
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:52,120
But why...

84
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:54,247
didn't I realize that sooner?

85
00:06:56,582 --> 00:07:01,087
Well, it's not like everyone
feels thankful for oxygen

86
00:07:01,170 --> 00:07:02,672
every time they breathe.

87
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:09,554
That just means that the fun you have
is so close to you that it feels natural.

88
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:14,100
Good thing you realized that
before you lost them for good.

89
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:17,395
I'm really relieved.

90
00:07:24,318 --> 00:07:27,071
Also, can I ask one more thing?

91
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:28,281
Hm?

92
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:30,408
If you knew that all along...

93
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:32,743
why did you still become the top?

94
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:44,839
Because I want to always have fun
eating together with everyone!

95
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:51,429
If everyone can be happy
and smile together...

96
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:53,890
then I can have my meal with joy.

97
00:07:57,393 --> 00:08:01,481
And when I thought about how
I could make that happen...

98
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:04,400
the answer was to become the top of Furin.

99
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:05,902
<i>That's all.</i>

100
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,947
It's not like I strived to become one.

101
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:13,242
It's just that I had something
I wanted to do by becoming the top.

102
00:08:13,326 --> 00:08:15,411
If there was another way
to make it happen,

103
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,497
I would've probably done that instead.

104
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:19,624
But if that was the case...

105
00:08:19,707 --> 00:08:22,960
I wouldn't have been able
to eat with you guys like this.

106
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:29,884
You're really amazing, Ume-chan!

107
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:33,429
You became the top while knowing
full well what you wanted to do.

108
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:35,848
Nah, I didn't "become" one.

109
00:08:39,268 --> 00:08:41,062
I was given the title.

110
00:08:43,022 --> 00:08:45,358
You can't become the top
when you're alone, right?

111
00:08:47,151 --> 00:08:51,614
<i>I only became the top
because everyone supported me.</i>

112
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:56,244
<i>They agreed with my vision
and wanted to help me.</i>

113
00:08:56,786 --> 00:09:00,581
<i>So when I became the top, I realized...</i>

114
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:04,835
<i>my dream was no longer just my own.</i>

115
00:09:05,878 --> 00:09:09,131
That is why... to make that dream a reality...

116
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:12,802
no matter how difficult,
no matter how unreasonable,

117
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:15,137
no matter how absurd the path is...

118
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:21,435
I will never lose.

119
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:38,661
You're really shouldering a lot
on your back, huh, Ume-chan?

120
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:41,414
Your fists are light.

121
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,791
Do you know why?

122
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:46,586
Because they don't shoulder anything.

123
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:50,172
Choji?

124
00:09:56,137 --> 00:09:59,515
No wonder my fists are so light.

125
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:02,685
I could never win against you.

126
00:10:07,815 --> 00:10:08,733
See ya!

127
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:11,068
You guys should come play
at our place next.

128
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:15,698
The stuff here was great, but we've
got a lot of great food over there, too!

129
00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:16,741
Really?

130
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:18,075
Of course!

131
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,620
I wish I brought something.

132
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:25,499
I forgot I brought the anpan from Cactus!

133
00:10:26,584 --> 00:10:27,418
Wanna try?

134
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:30,004
Their breads are still good
even when they're cold!

135
00:10:30,171 --> 00:10:33,924
I don't think being cold
is the problem at that point.

136
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:35,217
Thanks.

137
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:38,763
I'll treat you with
a freshly baked one next time!

138
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,572
See you later!

139
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:00,284
Later!

140
00:11:09,543 --> 00:11:10,961
There they go.

141
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:12,296
Yeah.

142
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:15,257
Hey, Kame-chan.

143
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:16,217
Hm?

144
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,969
I know.

145
00:11:20,429 --> 00:11:24,600
I know what I did can't be
forgiven with a simple "sorry."

146
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:27,311
Yeah.

147
00:11:27,436 --> 00:11:31,148
But I don't know what else I should do...

148
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:33,567
or what I can do...

149
00:11:34,735 --> 00:11:36,654
Even so...

150
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:38,531
I...

151
00:11:39,281 --> 00:11:40,950
need all of you.

152
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:43,244
So...

153
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:46,664
Me too.

154
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:49,917
I still did what I did.

155
00:11:51,585 --> 00:11:54,004
I want to make up for it...

156
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:58,050
But I don't know what I should do
after I apologize.

157
00:11:59,343 --> 00:12:02,179
But... that's why...

158
00:12:03,597 --> 00:12:06,308
I think we have to face the consequences.

159
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:13,232
Let's look for the answer.
Together this time.

160
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:18,821
Yeah!

161
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:28,539
What's the matter?

162
00:12:29,206 --> 00:12:32,793
Even after it's been crushed this badly,
it is still a proper anpan!

163
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:37,173
This is good!

164
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:39,550
I wonder how it tastes
when it's freshly baked.

165
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:55,107
Huh? It's raining again?

166
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:00,696
Oh, you're right.

167
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:02,114
It's so weird.

168
00:13:03,532 --> 00:13:07,661
Even though the sun parted the clouds...

169
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:12,374
<i>Welcome back.</i>

170
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:31,685
OMELET RICE - CURRY RICE - NAPOLITAN
SHRIMP PILAF - EGG SANDWICH - PIZZA TOAST

171
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:49,161
Wait, Sasaki? You were waiting
for us this whole time?

172
00:13:58,045 --> 00:14:00,256
I told you to leave it to us, didn't I?

173
00:14:02,758 --> 00:14:04,301
It's all over now.

174
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:11,225
Thank you...

175
00:14:11,976 --> 00:14:13,060
so...

176
00:14:13,769 --> 00:14:15,771
so much!

177
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,985
We're back!

178
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:22,528
Welcome ba...

179
00:14:22,611 --> 00:14:25,114
Huh, wait? You got all patched up already?

180
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:27,908
-Shishitoren wasn't much, then?
-Kotoha! I'm back!

181
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:30,411
Yeah. We're apparently... friends, now?

182
00:14:30,494 --> 00:14:32,538
You guys always go all out, huh?

183
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:34,498
Are you guys okay?

184
00:14:34,582 --> 00:14:36,292
This much is no big deal.

185
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,879
And you look pretty fine.

186
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:42,756
I don't sweat much.

187
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:45,676
And you look so beaten up, too, Sakura.

188
00:14:47,177 --> 00:14:48,512
Welcome back.

189
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:54,226
Because you are alone.

190
00:14:55,978 --> 00:15:00,232
I only became the top
because everyone supported me.

191
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:04,361
They agreed with my vision
and wanted to help me.

192
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,947
What's wrong, Sakura-san?

193
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,366
You've been awfully quiet
on the way back, too.

194
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:10,326
I'm leaving.

195
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:12,995
Huh? Sakura-san? What's the matter?

196
00:15:14,038 --> 00:15:15,456
Now hold it there.

197
00:15:15,539 --> 00:15:16,540
What?

198
00:15:16,624 --> 00:15:19,960
Today is a momentous day!
We gotta celebrate!

199
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:22,922
Kotoha! Make us some of your
special coffee, won't you?

200
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:28,177
There's nothing to celebrate!

201
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:30,554
You managed to converse
with your opponent today!

202
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:33,182
Today is your
"first fist conversation" anniversary!

203
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:36,060
Huh? You're making no sense!

204
00:15:36,143 --> 00:15:38,437
What's a "first fist conversation"
anniversary?

205
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:41,941
Hmm, maybe like the salad anniversary?

206
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:45,152
-If you want, then do it without me...
-I...

207
00:15:45,235 --> 00:15:47,404
want to talk with you.

208
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,953
<i>I thought you could become
the top all by yourself.</i>

209
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:58,082
<i>That the strongest one around
gets to be the top.</i>

210
00:15:58,999 --> 00:16:01,877
<i>But it seems like I was wrong.</i>

211
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:07,925
So, how was it?

212
00:16:08,008 --> 00:16:09,802
How was your talk with Togame?

213
00:16:12,012 --> 00:16:13,639
I told you I didn't talk with him.

214
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:16,266
I didn't hear any words from his fists.

215
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:24,483
Oh, I see. So that's how you took it?

216
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:27,653
You're quite the dreamer,
aren't you, Sakura-kun?

217
00:16:27,736 --> 00:16:30,114
Sakura-san, that's not
what he meant by that.

218
00:16:30,739 --> 00:16:32,992
What's with all of you? Stop laughing!

219
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:36,662
Sorry. It's my fault for
not explaining it to you properly.

220
00:16:37,121 --> 00:16:40,165
Still, you're pretty pure.

221
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:42,334
I wasn't talking about telepathy.

222
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:44,712
Not even I could hear anything
through punches.

223
00:16:48,424 --> 00:16:50,759
When I said fists are a type
of communication...

224
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,803
it doesn't mean verbal communication.

225
00:16:52,886 --> 00:16:56,849
I'm saying it's a means to let you express
your thoughts and feel other people's.

226
00:16:57,641 --> 00:17:01,770
<i>And because fists are a much primitive way
of communication compared to language,</i>

227
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:04,606
<i>things that you can express
would be just as primitive.</i>

228
00:17:04,732 --> 00:17:06,442
Primitive?

229
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:10,070
Like whether you like
the other person or not.

230
00:17:11,947 --> 00:17:13,115
My eyes!

231
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:14,491
Hold it, Sugishita.

232
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:16,744
Wow, he used poison breath!

233
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:19,163
Good grief, what are you guys doing?

234
00:17:19,246 --> 00:17:20,956
You better wipe it all off!

235
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:24,668
My bad, Kotoha.

236
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:31,842
You had a conversation with Togame
and grew to like him, didn't you?

237
00:17:32,926 --> 00:17:34,178
Huh?

238
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:39,475
And that's why you tried
to punch Tomiyama.

239
00:17:41,518 --> 00:17:45,272
I believe that's the proof that
you had a conversation with him.

240
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:50,027
So what? What if I managed to do that?

241
00:17:50,277 --> 00:17:52,780
Why do we gotta celebrate it?

242
00:17:53,113 --> 00:17:54,698
Well, because...

243
00:17:57,576 --> 00:17:59,203
that makes me happy!

244
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:00,579
Huh?

245
00:18:00,662 --> 00:18:04,708
You see, when I heard an outsider
moved into the town...

246
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:08,712
<i>I thought you were some weirdo,
so I was curious what you'd be like.</i>

247
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:16,428
After watching you for two days...

248
00:18:20,516 --> 00:18:22,267
You're a good guy.

249
00:18:23,602 --> 00:18:26,438
<i>And a good guy like you came to this town.</i>

250
00:18:27,523 --> 00:18:29,566
That makes me happy!

251
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:35,781
Then you could've just
called this a "welcoming party."

252
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:38,784
It's easier to get than
"first fist conversation" anniversary.

253
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:40,953
Oh, that's a good idea!

254
00:18:42,704 --> 00:18:43,956
You're right!

255
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:45,958
Why...

256
00:18:47,584 --> 00:18:50,045
How can you accept me so easily?

257
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:52,256
Letting me in...

258
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,716
<i>Everyone in this town...</i>

259
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:57,386
<i>And also the guys in Furin...</i>

260
00:18:58,178 --> 00:19:03,308
I came here to become the top,
to beat you and take your place!

261
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:09,273
I can't do what you're doing.

262
00:19:10,065 --> 00:19:14,486
<i>After all, I've never accepted
anyone in my life before.</i>

263
00:19:15,654 --> 00:19:18,991
<i>That was why I strove to
become stronger by myself.</i>

264
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:26,373
<i>I came here because I wanted to usurp
the top and accept myself for who I am.</i>

265
00:19:27,749 --> 00:19:29,084
<i>But...</i>

266
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:32,337
<i>Apparently, you need other people
in order to become the top.</i>

267
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:36,008
<i>And as someone who
can't accept other people...</i>

268
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:39,553
<i>I... could never...</i>

269
00:19:40,387 --> 00:19:42,764
Wait! Hold on, Sakura-san!

270
00:19:49,646 --> 00:19:51,148
Sakura-san!

271
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:54,776
Yesterday you said I wasn't pathetic!

272
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:59,489
<i>But well...
I suppose you're not all that pathetic.</i>

273
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:02,868
<i>You saw me for who I am!</i>

274
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:05,871
That made me really happy!

275
00:20:07,122 --> 00:20:09,124
So, Sakura-san, you...

276
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:14,755
Huh? What was I trying to say again?

277
00:20:14,922 --> 00:20:17,591
It's okay. I think he gets it.

278
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:20,761
Hey, Sakura.

279
00:20:20,844 --> 00:20:24,014
Do you know the requirements
to talk with your fists?

280
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:25,474
Requirements?

281
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:27,976
It's to face the other person.

282
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:29,937
To want to know more about them.

283
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:32,356
And you accomplished that.

284
00:20:33,857 --> 00:20:36,318
That's why you were able
to converse with Togame.

285
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:38,028
<i>I want to know.</i>

286
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:39,738
<i>I want to know more about him.</i>

287
00:20:40,697 --> 00:20:44,243
You don't necessarily need to accept
everything about the other person.

288
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:49,081
But to accept someone,
you have to face them first.

289
00:20:50,415 --> 00:20:52,960
You're a guy who can do that,

290
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:55,629
and it looks to me that
you want to accept others.

291
00:20:56,546 --> 00:20:59,299
You haven't given up on other people.

292
00:20:59,383 --> 00:21:00,842
You don't have to.

293
00:21:01,468 --> 00:21:03,553
You should lift your face up to us, too.

294
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:04,763
Once you do, I'm sure...

295
00:21:04,846 --> 00:21:07,975
<i>And if you can do that,
you can become anything you want to be.</i>

296
00:21:09,017 --> 00:21:11,728
<i>You can even be the top!</i>

297
00:21:12,562 --> 00:21:13,814
Okay?

298
00:21:26,743 --> 00:21:31,498
If I become the top, that
would mean you lose to me!

299
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:36,086
I guess so! Well, let's worry
about that when the time comes!

300
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:40,340
Huh? What's up, Sugishita? Bathroom?

301
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:42,843
I'll crush you!

302
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:45,470
Huh? You wanna go? Bring it on!

303
00:21:46,555 --> 00:21:48,598
Sugishita-san! Wait!

304
00:21:48,682 --> 00:21:50,976
He's been glaring him
this whole time, after all.

305
00:21:51,059 --> 00:21:54,313
Hey! What are you guys doing?

306
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:57,399
If you wanna fight, take it outside!

307
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:34,496
{\an8}Umemiya sure is weak against Kotoha.

308
00:23:34,788 --> 00:23:36,373
{\an8}Yeah.

309
00:23:36,456 --> 00:23:40,377
{\an8}That means Bofurin's top is...

310
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:45,465
You finally realized, huh?

